<subSubSection id="7FF7652D8B31FFEDA21CAED1FE5876AD" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="375236A68B31FFEDA21CAED1FE5876AD" blockId="7.[113,1089,326,745]" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA21CAED1FF65758D" bold="true" box="[113,224,434,457]" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">Remarks.</emphasis>
Validity of this species requires further study as we examined only the 
<typeStatus id="E85688048B31FFEDA1B2AED1FBC4758D" box="[991,1089,434,457]" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">lectotype</typeStatus>
which is female and hence we could not compare aedeagi, which are often diagnostic in 
<taxonomicName id="F0ED4D258B31FFEDA21CAE91FE9D764D" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" box="[113,280,498,521]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA21CAE91FE9D764D" box="[113,280,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen has a postsctutellar spot as in 
<taxonomicName id="F0ED4D258B31FFEDA161AE91FC28764D" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[780,941,498,521]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multisignata">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA161AE91FC28764D" box="[780,941,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">P. multisignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, all elytral spots are pale yellow (humeral, middle four and posterior four red in the latter). The red color in elytra of some museum specimens has vanished, however, we have examined numerous historical specimens and the red color was always distinct in fully sclerotized individuals. The 
<typeStatus id="E85688048B31FFEDA34AAD11FE0C76CD" box="[295,393,626,649]" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F0ED4D258B31FFEDA3C3AD11FD9C76CD" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[430,537,626,649]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scenica">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA3C3AD11FD9C76CD" box="[430,537,626,649]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">P. scenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a fully sclerotized specimen entirely lacking red color. Also, 
<taxonomicName id="F0ED4D258B31FFEDA29EADF1FE1776ED" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[243,402,658,681]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multisignata">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA29EADF1FE1776ED" box="[243,402,658,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">P. multisignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always has large elytra spots while these are small in 
<taxonomicName id="F0ED4D258B31FFEDA1BBADF1FBC476ED" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[982,1089,658,681]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scenica">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA1BBADF1FBC476ED" box="[982,1089,658,681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">P. scenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore we assume it is a distinct species from both 
<taxonomicName id="F0ED4D258B31FFEDA088ADD1FC00768D" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[741,901,690,713]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multisignata">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA088ADD1FC00768D" box="[741,901,690,713]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">P. multisignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F0ED4D258B31FFEDA1D6ADD1FBBF768D" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[955,1082,690,713]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="750" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahlbergi">
<emphasis id="0599EAB48B31FFEDA1D6ADD1FBBF768D" box="[955,1082,690,713]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="750">P. sahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For further characters see 
<tableCitation id="7A6F031D8B31FFEDA3EAADB1FE5276AD" box="[391,471,722,745]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="3.[112,159,995,1014]" captionText="Table 1. Characters distinguishing the three revalidated Plagiometriona species." pageId="7" pageNumber="750">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
